Aim: To solve a linear system of tridiagonal equations using the Thomas Algorithm (tridiagonal matrix algorithm or TDMA) and to plot the results using MATLAB.

Objective: The main objective is to implement the Thomas Algorithm in MATLAB and analyze its effectiveness in solving tridiagonal linear systems.

Algorithm: Thomas Algorithm (Step by Step)
1. Initialize the given tridiagonal matrix, right-hand side vector and the solution vector.
2. Perform forward elimination:
   a. Calculate the ratios: c(i) = c(i)/(b(i) - a(i) * c(i - 1)), and d(i) = (d(i) - a(i) * d(i - 1))/(b(i) - a(i) * c(i - 1)) for i = 2 to n.
3. Perform backward substitution:
   a. Calculate the solution: x(n) = d(n), x(i) = d(i) - c(i) * x(i + 1) for i = n - 1 to 1.

MATLAB Code for Thomas Algorithm:

```MATLAB
function x = thomas_algorithm(a, b, c, d)
    n = length(d);
    x = zeros(n, 1);

    % Forward elimination
    for i = 2:n
        ratio = a(i)/(b(i - 1) - a(i - 1) * c(i - 1));
        c(i) = c(i)/ratio;
        d(i) = (d(i) - a(i) * d(i - 1))/ratio;
    end

    % Backward substitution
    x(n) = d(n);
    for i = n - 1:-1:1
        x(i) = d(i) - c(i) * x(i + 1);
    end
end
```

