4. We open the webcam and display it in a window using the `JFrame` class. We also capture an image from the webcam and save it to a file using the `BufferedImage` and `File` classes.

5. Finally, we close the webcam, dispose of the window, and exit the program.

Note that in some cases, the user may need to run the program with administrator privileges to grant access to the camera on macOS.

